Unlithified, greenish gray homogenous wackestone with both fine sand and coarse sand size grains. There is color variability (olivegray, light olive gray, dark greenish gray) and patchiness at a scale larger than any burrow previously observed. This interval continues into the upper 10 cm of Section 2. Pyrite is disseminated in the matrix but it is also concentrated in a few burrows. Pyrite nodules (few mm long) also present. Occasional small benthic forams and shell fragments

Unlithified wackestone with fine sand size grains. Contact and color change at 10 cm and at 125 cm. Above 10 cm it is light olive gray and homogeneous, Coarser sand and a 2 cm long pyritized bivalve occur at the contact. From 10-125 cm there is patchiness and color variability (olive gray, light olive gray, greenish gray). From 10-125 cm there is sparse disseminated pyrite, benthic forams and a sea urchin spine. Below 125 cm it is greenish gray and homogeneous
